WEBVTT

00:02.480 --> 00:06.041
People keep asking me questions
that I don't know the answer to.

00:06.240 --> 00:08.891
It's us that has the machine guns now.

00:09.600 --> 00:11.409
And it's them that's in the mud.

00:12.640 --> 00:14.130
Guns, Mr Shelby.

00:14.200 --> 00:15.770
We'd pay good money.

00:15.840 --> 00:18.571
- For who do you speak?
- The Irish Republican Army.

00:20.960 --> 00:23.122
What are you? Copper?

00:23.200 --> 00:24.486
(GUNSHOT)

00:25.240 --> 00:27.720
You went after him because he was IRA.

00:27.800 --> 00:30.167
I followed him because I thought
he might have information.

00:31.640 --> 00:34.120
<i>CAMPBELL". The difficulty
with undercover work, Grace,</i>

00:34.200 --> 00:36.248
<i>is to remember what you are.</i>

00:36.760 --> 00:37.807
(GROANING)

00:38.040 --> 00:40.805
Your sister's in there giving birth,
there's one man should be here.

00:40.880 --> 00:41.881
TOMMY: You're right, Pol.

00:41.960 --> 00:43.928
On my oath. Tell Freddie it's safe.

00:46.160 --> 00:47.491
Welcome to the world, son.

00:48.560 --> 00:50.528
- Freddie!
- THORNE: Ada!

00:50.880 --> 00:52.245
Polly! Polly!

00:52.320 --> 00:53.810
The police came
and took his father away!

00:55.280 --> 00:56.645
(S PITS) You liar!

01:19.760 --> 01:25.847
<i># Take a little walk to the edge of town
and go across the track</i>

01:27.480 --> 01:31.565
<i># Where the viaduct looms
like a bird of doom</i>

01:31.640 --> 01:34.723
<i># As it shifts and cracks</i>

01:35.800 --> 01:40.124
<i># Where secrets lie in the border fires</i>

01:40.200 --> 01:42.123
<i># In the humming wires</i>

01:42.200 --> 01:45.443
<i># Hey man, you know
you're never coming back</i>

01:45.520 --> 01:47.522
<i># Past the square, past the bridge</i>

01:47.600 --> 01:50.490
<i># Past the mills, past the stacks</i>

01:52.360 --> 01:57.082
<i># On a gathering storm comes
a tall handsome man</i>

01:57.160 --> 02:01.245
<i># In a dusty black coat with
a red right hand #</i>

02:19.840 --> 02:20.841
(SIGHS)

02:26.600 --> 02:27.601
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

02:27.720 --> 02:28.721
Open up, love.

02:30.200 --> 02:31.884
I brought more things
for you and the baby.

02:31.960 --> 02:33.086
Got some fresh eggs and bread.

02:33.520 --> 02:34.760
-(BABY CRIES)
- Shh...

02:34.840 --> 02:36.171
POLLY: I'll leave it here.

02:36.320 --> 02:37.481
(BABY CRYING)

02:37.560 --> 02:39.847
Ada, think of the little one.

02:41.400 --> 02:43.482
Babies don't have principles.

03:06.120 --> 03:07.121
(DOOR OPENS)

03:12.400 --> 03:13.845
Did you speak to her?

03:15.040 --> 03:16.883
She didn't speak back.

03:19.840 --> 03:21.490
Did you tell her?

03:22.840 --> 03:25.286
I'll only tell her
what I know to be true.

03:27.880 --> 03:30.121
It's the last time
I'm going to say this.

03:30.280 --> 03:32.965
It wasn't me who shot Freddie Thorne.

03:35.640 --> 03:36.641
Tommy.

03:37.120 --> 03:39.441
I'd ask you to swear on the Bible

03:39.520 --> 03:41.204
but you can't swear on that, can you?

03:42.480 --> 03:43.845
Nothing you hold sacred.

03:49.560 --> 03:51.005
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

03:54.600 --> 03:55.601
There's tea.

04:01.720 --> 04:03.085
A new system.

04:04.080 --> 04:05.570
Everything in the diary, eh?

04:06.080 --> 04:07.081
Mmm-hmm.

04:12.280 --> 04:13.281
Black star.

04:13.520 --> 04:14.851
What does that mean?

04:15.320 --> 04:16.321
Black star day...

04:17.519 --> 04:20.204
is the day we take out Billy Kimber
and his men.

04:21.279 --> 04:22.770
No one knows this.

04:23.760 --> 04:25.524
Not even your family?

04:26.840 --> 04:28.205
Grace...

04:30.800 --> 04:32.689
Everyone in my family hates me.

04:33.680 --> 04:36.160
Why would I tell them?

04:36.240 --> 04:37.241
(DOOR CLOSES)

04:37.920 --> 04:39.285
He's off the bloody rails
is what he is.

04:39.360 --> 04:40.361
(MEN CHEERING)

04:40.440 --> 04:42.488
If he'll turn nose on his best mate.

04:42.560 --> 04:45.245
Bloody neighbours, john.
Snitch behind the curtain.

04:45.640 --> 04:49.326
Yeah, well, if you think that,
you're the only one who does.

04:49.560 --> 04:51.164
Look at this. Look.

04:51.240 --> 04:52.924
Bloody rakin' it in!

04:53.000 --> 04:54.445
Who's running this carny?

04:54.520 --> 04:57.842
Name of Marsden. Intends on wintering
in Small Heath at this ring.

04:57.920 --> 04:59.524
- Does he?
- Only heard.

04:59.760 --> 05:04.607
Nobody in Small Heath craps in a pot
without the decree of Tommy Almighty.

05:05.040 --> 05:06.644
Mr Marsden, I believe!

05:07.200 --> 05:08.281
The ring master!

05:08.720 --> 05:10.085
Proud I am to say so.

05:10.160 --> 05:12.162
Yeah, well, these here
are civilised parts.

05:12.960 --> 05:16.123
Man wants to set his stall up
with fellas lampin' each other.

05:16.200 --> 05:18.009
He needs himself a license.

05:18.240 --> 05:19.287
A license?

05:20.600 --> 05:21.601
For a fee.

05:22.600 --> 05:23.965
From those in charge.

05:24.040 --> 05:25.121
(CROWD CH EERING)

05:25.760 --> 05:26.807
I'll tell you what.

05:26.880 --> 05:30.566
How about I keep my money and you
shove a license up your arse crack?

05:30.720 --> 05:32.609
You don't want to speak to me like that.

05:32.680 --> 05:34.045
And who the bloody hell
do you think you are?

05:34.120 --> 05:35.167
(MAN SHOUTING) My name...

05:35.640 --> 05:37.244
is Arthur Shelby!

05:39.200 --> 05:40.201
Dad?

05:46.840 --> 05:47.841
Jesus.

05:53.240 --> 05:54.651
Thank you. You're a good boy.

05:57.200 --> 05:58.247
(SIGHS)

05:58.320 --> 06:00.800
Bless the father for these bounties
we're about to receive...

06:00.880 --> 06:02.370
Jesus Christ.

06:02.440 --> 06:03.601
Please, woman.

06:04.520 --> 06:05.681
Let me be.

06:06.560 --> 06:08.005
Finish your sandwich
and sling your hook.

06:10.120 --> 06:13.886
Polly Anna, I'm a guest
of the head of this family.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.169
So why don't you maybe tend to your
mangle or your scuttle?

06:17.240 --> 06:18.730
The head of the family ain't here.

06:23.520 --> 06:24.521
Tommy, Uh.

06:24.760 --> 06:26.683
Sometimes helps me with, uh,

06:27.200 --> 06:28.929
with business.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.001
(DOOR OPENS)

06:30.680 --> 06:33.445
-(DOOR CLOSES)
- Aye, well, speak of the devil.

06:35.520 --> 06:36.885
How are you, son?

06:38.760 --> 06:39.761
Get out.

06:40.840 --> 06:41.841
Come on, son.

06:42.880 --> 06:44.245
I'm a changed man.

06:45.360 --> 06:47.966
This family needed you 10 years ago.

06:48.640 --> 06:50.130
And you walked out on us.

06:50.720 --> 06:51.721
Not now.

06:52.040 --> 06:53.041
Get out of this house.

06:53.480 --> 06:55.323
- Tommy, he's different.
- Shut up.

06:58.760 --> 07:00.171
It's all right, son.

07:01.800 --> 07:03.086
Arthur Shelby...

07:04.120 --> 07:05.963
never stays where he's not welcome.

07:09.920 --> 07:10.921
(IN HALES SHARPLY)

07:11.920 --> 07:13.649
Quite something you've become.

07:19.520 --> 07:20.521
Bye,son.

07:29.520 --> 07:30.521
(DOOR CLOSES)

07:32.080 --> 07:33.650
- He's our dad.
-(SCOFFS)

07:35.720 --> 07:37.643
He's a selfish bastard.

07:39.480 --> 07:41.528
You calling someone a selfish bastard?

07:43.680 --> 07:45.250
It's a bit rich, Tommy.

07:45.600 --> 07:46.601
I mean, thanks to you,

07:48.240 --> 07:50.720
we're already down a bloody sister.

07:51.480 --> 07:53.130
You want to see him, Arthur?

07:53.200 --> 07:54.611
You want to see him?

07:55.640 --> 07:56.641
You go with him.

08:12.880 --> 08:15.008
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

08:23.520 --> 08:24.521
(DOOR OPENS)

08:26.280 --> 08:27.281
Grace.

08:27.840 --> 08:30.684
I'm taking five pounds
from petty cash, all right?

08:30.760 --> 08:32.683
We don't have five pounds
in petty cash.

08:32.760 --> 08:34.524
Then I'll take what we've got.

08:34.840 --> 08:36.251
Count it and leave a receipt.

08:38.480 --> 08:41.563
Arthur, there are things in these books
I don't understand.

08:41.760 --> 08:42.807
Likewise.

08:42.880 --> 08:46.566
Every week we pay one pound,
ten shilling by postal order

08:47.360 --> 08:48.361
to a Daniel Owen

08:49.040 --> 08:50.769
-in London.
- Danny Whizz-Bang.

08:51.080 --> 08:53.765
Hangs around in the pubs
in Camden Town Wharf for us.

08:54.320 --> 08:57.085
Keeps his ears open for business.
He's a good man.

08:57.160 --> 08:58.605
I thought Danny Whizz-Bang was dead?

08:58.680 --> 09:00.523
Then you thought wrong, didn't you?

09:00.880 --> 09:02.769
But I've seen his grave. He was shot.

09:03.560 --> 09:05.927
That was a show to satisfy the wops.

09:06.480 --> 09:08.801
Tommyjust shot
some sheep's brains at him.

09:10.240 --> 09:11.651
Who's buried in his grave?

09:16.440 --> 09:17.771
Now look, Grace.

09:18.600 --> 09:19.726
You know what's good for you.

09:19.880 --> 09:23.248
You don't ask questions about things
that don't concern you.

09:24.240 --> 09:25.685
Never, right?

09:26.720 --> 09:27.846
That's for you.

09:28.480 --> 09:30.687
Don't tell Tommy I took this.

10:00.320 --> 10:02.527
The boy needs a good hiding
if you ask me.

10:02.600 --> 10:04.841
Yeah, well, I'm this close
to giving him one.

10:05.640 --> 10:07.210
John and Ada too, sounds like.

10:07.280 --> 10:09.487
Nah,john moans on bloody principle.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.650
But if you saw his missus...

10:13.160 --> 10:14.207
Ah...

10:14.960 --> 10:16.769
You have a girl yourself, son?

10:20.040 --> 10:21.690
Perhaps when it suits, Tommy, eh?

10:24.080 --> 10:25.081
Yeah, well.

10:25.840 --> 10:27.330
He's been different.

10:27.880 --> 10:29.848
- You know, since the war.
- Yeah, well...

10:30.760 --> 10:32.489
A war can change a man.

10:33.240 --> 10:35.049
Speaking for myself, anyways.

10:35.120 --> 10:36.201
Where did you fight, Dad?

10:37.320 --> 10:39.084
Ah, all over, son.

10:39.520 --> 10:41.887
- All over.
- Yea h, all over.

10:41.960 --> 10:44.361
And the salvation ofjesus Christ

10:45.440 --> 10:47.442
spread his light over me.

10:48.120 --> 10:49.121
And as a pilgrim,

10:49.960 --> 10:51.849
I come to visit a new world.

10:52.440 --> 10:53.441
America.

10:54.040 --> 10:56.088
Where I beheld the future.

10:59.040 --> 11:00.041
Casinos.

11:00.160 --> 11:01.969
Money factories, son.

11:02.360 --> 11:05.489
Look, I've been studying
the competition.

11:07.080 --> 11:08.081
Their schemes,

11:08.720 --> 11:09.801
their systems.

11:10.040 --> 11:12.008
- Look at that. It's all there.
- Show me.

11:13.160 --> 11:15.481
There's a fortune to be made here.

11:17.120 --> 11:19.771
I'm an old man and my
heart's a battered vessel.

11:20.440 --> 11:21.441
But within,

11:23.400 --> 11:26.085
there still beats a fluttering
pulse of a dream.

11:28.360 --> 11:29.805
The Shelby...

11:29.880 --> 11:32.201
Casino and Hotel.

11:32.840 --> 11:36.128
Gents and dames will come flocking
from all corners.

11:37.080 --> 11:40.641
New York, Chicago, Boston,

11:40.880 --> 11:41.881
to the Shelby.

11:42.400 --> 11:46.325
Where I can stand proudly with
my dear children by my side.

11:47.360 --> 11:48.850
And the women there?

11:50.800 --> 11:52.529
Like fresh peaches.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.525
Thou could have a dozen.

11:57.680 --> 11:59.284
We'd all of us be kings.

12:00.120 --> 12:01.929
How much? How much to get started?

12:03.040 --> 12:05.202
The oak needs but an acorn.

12:07.480 --> 12:08.481
Let's do it.

12:09.800 --> 12:11.848
Let's do it. Let's bloody do it.

12:11.960 --> 12:15.681
It would make my heart beam, but
I don't want to cause any discord

12:15.760 --> 12:19.481
between the brothers. So please,
why don't you talk to Tommy first?

12:19.720 --> 12:21.882
No, now, I'm sick of taking
orders from him.

12:22.640 --> 12:25.689
Tommy's not the only one in the
family with a head for business.

12:27.800 --> 12:28.881
And Shelby money

12:30.160 --> 12:31.764
is Shelby money.

12:32.440 --> 12:35.922
I thank God for my wonderful sons.

12:37.880 --> 12:39.848
This is cause for a celebration.

12:39.920 --> 12:41.763
<i>- Yeah.
- Sla'inte.</i>

12:41.840 --> 12:43.205
<i>Sl√©inte.</i>

12:49.360 --> 12:51.249
On your feet, soldier.

12:52.600 --> 12:54.602
On your feet.

12:57.040 --> 12:58.451
(RAUCOUS SHOUTING)

13:01.400 --> 13:02.686
Look, I don't wanna fight you, Dad.

13:02.760 --> 13:04.046
Come on, boy!

13:04.120 --> 13:05.884
I'm old enough to be your father.

13:13.760 --> 13:14.886
(GRUNTS)

13:15.600 --> 13:16.601
MAN: On your feet!

13:18.000 --> 13:19.126
Get up!

13:20.200 --> 13:21.201
All right!

13:23.720 --> 13:25.245
(CROWD CH EERING)

13:28.000 --> 13:29.081
(GRUNTING)

13:32.840 --> 13:34.808
Is that all you got, boy?

13:41.400 --> 13:42.481
Get up!

13:53.840 --> 13:54.966
(SHOUTS) This here...

13:55.320 --> 13:57.368
is Arthur Shelby junior!

13:57.680 --> 13:58.761
MY Son!

13:59.280 --> 14:01.601
I love him and I'm proud of him!

14:01.840 --> 14:04.491
And he can fight any
one of youse in here!

14:05.120 --> 14:06.246
(CROWD CHEERS)

14:12.920 --> 14:14.001
You did good, son.

14:14.440 --> 14:15.441
You did good.

14:16.160 --> 14:17.161
I love you, Dad.

14:17.760 --> 14:20.047
I love you!

14:37.840 --> 14:38.841
Mr Shelby?

14:40.640 --> 14:41.641
Who's asking?

14:42.760 --> 14:43.761
My name's Burn.

14:45.600 --> 14:48.251
I had word from your man in Camden town
you wanted a parley.

14:50.280 --> 14:51.645
Then parley it is.

14:54.080 --> 14:55.161
Few months ago,

14:55.280 --> 14:58.250
a man named Ryan came to this place with
a view to buying some goods from you.

14:59.720 --> 15:01.529
Mr Ryan met with an accident,
he was shot.

15:02.400 --> 15:03.401
TOMMY: I heard.

15:03.680 --> 15:06.251
BURN: He was a man with a quick mouth.
I know that.

15:07.160 --> 15:09.162
Wondered if he made
any enemies in here?

15:09.240 --> 15:10.526
None that I know of.

15:11.080 --> 15:13.128
Not the kind of place to make enemies.

15:13.200 --> 15:15.726
- All are welcome here, Mr Burn.
- Including Irish?

15:16.400 --> 15:18.209
Oh, especially Irish.

15:20.040 --> 15:23.010
Ryan told you he was a member
of the Irish Republican Army.

15:23.360 --> 15:25.203
Was he still welcome?

15:25.280 --> 15:27.965
Like I say. Any man who buys
beer is welcome.

15:28.040 --> 15:29.849
Perhaps you didn't believe him?

15:35.240 --> 15:38.084
In pubs, sometimes people say things.

15:38.160 --> 15:39.969
Sometimes it's the whisky talking.

15:40.160 --> 15:42.322
It's hard to tell which is which.

15:43.720 --> 15:46.041
As a teetotal man, I find that amusing.

15:46.760 --> 15:49.286
Except when it ends in tragedy.

15:49.360 --> 15:51.169
Would you like some water
and cordial, Mr Burn?

15:51.520 --> 15:52.726
You see, Mr Shelby,

15:53.520 --> 15:57.445
Ryan, for all his quick mouth,
was indeed connected.

15:58.880 --> 16:01.008
Very well connected to our brotherhood.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.411
By membership in blood.

16:04.040 --> 16:05.326
He was my cousin.

16:06.800 --> 16:08.768
I'm from South Armagh.

16:10.680 --> 16:12.284
I'm a man of influence there.

16:13.600 --> 16:15.409
Cordial and water will
be grand, Mr Shelby.

16:19.160 --> 16:22.642
Grace, bring some water and cordial.
Come this way.

16:22.720 --> 16:23.801
Yes, Mr Shelby.

16:36.360 --> 16:38.283
My cousin came to buy guns.

16:38.360 --> 16:40.442
And I told him I have none.

16:41.400 --> 16:43.687
Your man Danny Owen
talks a lot when he's drunk.

16:46.240 --> 16:48.402
He says the Peaky Blinders
do have the guns,

16:48.520 --> 16:50.329
brought from the factory down the road.

16:50.600 --> 16:52.568
He boasted about a stack
of Lewis machine guns,

16:52.640 --> 16:55.086
and enough belts of ammunition
to hold up God's trousers.

16:56.160 --> 16:58.401
Yup, that sounds like our Danny.

16:59.120 --> 17:00.963
- He has an imagination.
-(DOOR OPENS)

17:01.400 --> 17:05.246
Like I say, sometimes it's
the whisky does the talk.

17:15.599 --> 17:17.807
He says only your brothers
know where the guns are kept.

17:18.560 --> 17:23.691
Well, Danny also says he sees German
infantrymen on the back of mill carts.

17:24.359 --> 17:26.362
And he shoots them with his broomstick.

17:28.520 --> 17:31.251
We have men in the BSA factory.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.764
They said you has 'em.

17:34.440 --> 17:36.681
And we have men that work
in the police station.

17:37.560 --> 17:39.688
Every finger, Mr Shelby...

17:40.400 --> 17:43.882
Every finger in this city
points in one direction.

17:46.160 --> 17:48.049
Please don't mistake me for a fool.

18:04.040 --> 18:06.008
Let me get to the point.

18:06.240 --> 18:10.962
I don't care what kind of half-arsed
tinker operation you have going here.

18:11.920 --> 18:13.285
But I can assure you,

18:14.280 --> 18:17.045
I represent a very different
category of organisation.

18:19.720 --> 18:22.087
My cousin was shot.

18:23.400 --> 18:26.529
I am judge, jury, and executioner.

18:27.000 --> 18:29.367
I find you guilty and I pass sentence.

18:30.600 --> 18:32.125
You deliver the guns to me,

18:33.240 --> 18:36.687
or I deliver death
and hell's fury to you,

18:36.760 --> 18:39.001
and your little tribe of heathens.

18:39.440 --> 18:41.488
Am I making myself clear?

18:54.760 --> 18:58.651
Let me confess something to you,
and only to you.

19:01.040 --> 19:05.284
I have the guns, but they have
become a burden to me.

19:08.040 --> 19:10.964
Perhaps it is time
to unload that burden.

19:12.720 --> 19:14.643
For the right price.

19:26.840 --> 19:28.490
(IN DISTINCT TALKING)

19:29.560 --> 19:30.846
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

19:39.800 --> 19:41.928
CAMPBELL: Malachy Burn.

19:42.000 --> 19:45.482
Brigade Commander
of the South Armagh IRA.

19:46.880 --> 19:48.689
You hooked yourself a big fish there.

19:48.760 --> 19:51.764
With these guns as bait,
who knows what we'll catch?

19:51.840 --> 19:53.524
We?

19:53.640 --> 19:57.884
Are you suggesting that you and I
could work together as a team?

19:58.080 --> 20:00.845
Perhaps we have more in common
than you think, Inspector.

20:01.880 --> 20:04.929
- Can you deliver him?
- With your help.

20:05.160 --> 20:08.403
And I want word put out in Ireland
that I was not involved.

20:10.000 --> 20:12.810
CAMPBELL: So I'd be solving
a problem for you.

20:12.920 --> 20:14.888
TOMMY: And I'd be
winning you that medal.

20:15.000 --> 20:21.246
(LAUGHS) If I get a medal, I will have
your initials engraved on my backside.

20:21.600 --> 20:27.289
Oh. My initials on your backside.
That's quite an image.

20:29.280 --> 20:32.568
Inspector, since we're
getting on so well...

20:32.640 --> 20:34.961
can you answer me a question?

20:35.040 --> 20:37.486
Who gave you Freddie Thorne?

20:37.560 --> 20:42.282
Well, as everyone in the city knows...
It was you, Mr Shelby.

20:58.320 --> 21:00.004
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

21:11.920 --> 21:15.720
- Hello, son.
- It's all there.

21:18.480 --> 21:22.610
It is indeed. We're gonna build
something with this, son.

21:23.080 --> 21:26.050
- Something magnificent.
- When do we start, Dad?

21:26.120 --> 21:28.202
- Hungry for work, are you?
- Yeah!

21:28.520 --> 21:30.807
Ship sails Friday.
Meet me at the boxing ring.

21:30.880 --> 21:33.565
- Good.Fflday.
- Ffiday.

21:50.960 --> 21:52.644
(BANGING ON DOOR)

22:07.800 --> 22:09.609
No, leave that open.

22:16.680 --> 22:17.727
(TOMMY PANTING)

22:20.800 --> 22:22.962
- No.
- Are you expecting trouble?

22:23.560 --> 22:24.846
- Yeah.
- At this hour?

22:24.920 --> 22:28.003
- Midnight is as good an hour as any.
- What the hell is going on?

22:28.080 --> 22:30.845
When the St Andrews' bell
strikes midnight,

22:30.920 --> 22:33.241
two IRA men are going
to come through that door.

22:33.320 --> 22:36.802
When they have what they want,
they plan to kill me.

22:37.160 --> 22:38.844
It's your job
to stop that happening.

22:38.920 --> 22:40.285
Could have given me
some more warning.

22:40.360 --> 22:43.842
I just got the message myself.
They want to meet here, alone.

22:43.920 --> 22:47.083
- And barmaids don't count?
- No, barmaids don't count, no.

22:47.240 --> 22:50.323
You're going to be in that back room.
I'm going to be sitting there.

22:51.040 --> 22:53.725
When I make a toast, you're going
to come out with that thing raised.

22:53.800 --> 22:56.610
You don't shoot, you just point.
I'll do the rest.

22:57.400 --> 23:00.006
- Will you kill them?
- No. The police want them alive.

23:00.080 --> 23:02.447
- The police know about this?
- Look, just hold it up.

23:02.720 --> 23:05.121
Just Point, right?

23:05.200 --> 23:09.046
-(BELL TOLLING)
- Right, go, go! Go on, go!

23:24.480 --> 23:26.482
(BELL TOLLING)

23:35.360 --> 23:36.930
We'll hold back here.

23:37.000 --> 23:40.971
If damage is done to either side,
it's no concern of ours.

24:14.560 --> 24:18.042
- Lost your thirst, eh?
-just show us where.

24:23.880 --> 24:25.609
Give me the cash.

24:35.440 --> 24:37.283
You're gonna need a shovel.

24:46.600 --> 24:47.886
<i>(caucus)</i>

24:50.360 --> 24:54.445
You thick fucking tinker.
Do you think we'd let you live?

24:56.080 --> 24:58.731
Make your peace, Mr Shelby.

25:02.120 --> 25:03.929
TOMMY: I'll make my peace my own way.

25:10.000 --> 25:12.048
To barmaids who don't count.

25:17.240 --> 25:18.810
(MEN GRUNTING)

25:26.480 --> 25:27.686
(GRACE GRUNTS)

25:28.680 --> 25:30.330
(MEN GRUNTING)

25:48.760 --> 25:49.761
<i>(SRO ANS)</i>

25:55.120 --> 25:56.167
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

26:07.160 --> 26:08.446
(MAN SHOUTING)

26:11.240 --> 26:12.241
<i>(SRO ANS)</i>

26:16.200 --> 26:17.850
(GROANING)

26:22.160 --> 26:23.491
(BONES CRACKING)

26:47.080 --> 26:48.525
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

27:06.640 --> 27:10.690
Why did you shoot?
Why did you shoot, Grace?

27:11.480 --> 27:14.404
I didn't know I had it in me
like that. I didn't... (SOBS)

27:16.320 --> 27:18.288
Now you've seen me.

27:21.880 --> 27:23.484
And you've seen me.

27:26.200 --> 27:27.486
I'm sorry.

27:36.040 --> 27:37.690
(DOOR OPENS)

27:45.360 --> 27:47.488
You were supposed to come
on the sixth chime.

27:47.560 --> 27:51.042
You were supposed to come
on the fucking sixth chime!

27:57.080 --> 27:58.491
They refused to surrender.

28:00.920 --> 28:02.922
They fought well, they were brave men.

28:05.080 --> 28:08.766
Well, he looks like he was killed
by a wild fucking animal.

28:10.240 --> 28:16.407
Still. This never happened.
They were never here. Who cares?

28:16.760 --> 28:18.683
Get the bodies out of here.

28:18.760 --> 28:21.923
Ah, right. Are they making
the lady uncomfortable?

28:23.400 --> 28:25.880
I'll leave you two
love birds to it, then, eh?

29:14.480 --> 29:15.641
Thank you.

29:19.960 --> 29:21.166
I'm sorry.

29:37.360 --> 29:40.011
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

29:59.680 --> 30:01.205
First of all, let me say...

30:02.320 --> 30:05.529
I had no idea he would
involve you in this ugly business.

30:05.600 --> 30:08.570
If I had, I never would
have let it happen.

30:08.640 --> 30:11.849
He trusts me. I told you that.
You didn't believe me.

30:12.600 --> 30:13.726
Fine.

30:15.080 --> 30:18.004
Sergeant Moss made a report,
which, of course, I burnt.

30:18.600 --> 30:22.082
He said that when he entered
the room, you were embracing.

30:22.760 --> 30:26.685
(SCOFFS) Is that your primary
concern, now? An embrace?

30:28.480 --> 30:32.201
- No, my concern is for your welfare.
- It was me who killed them.

30:34.920 --> 30:39.289
- I had no control.
- You've been living with beasts.

30:40.920 --> 30:43.082
It was the beast that tried to stop me.

30:50.120 --> 30:53.602
I believe, last night,
something inside me changed.

30:54.200 --> 30:56.885
I no longer feel the need
to avenge my father.

30:57.720 --> 31:00.087
The hatred that I brought
here with me is gone.

31:02.400 --> 31:04.562
And therefore my reasons
for joining the Service.

31:05.000 --> 31:06.445
You want to resign?

31:08.160 --> 31:10.162
I think our mission has come
to a natural end.

31:13.040 --> 31:15.520
I think I know where
the guns are hidden.

31:15.760 --> 31:17.967
You do? So tell me where!

31:18.040 --> 31:19.565
If I'm right and the guns are found,

31:19.640 --> 31:22.405
you have no more business
with Thomas Shelby. <i>Is</i> that not so?

31:23.000 --> 31:26.482
Our military mission will be over, and
we can leave the city as we found it.

31:28.480 --> 31:31.962
Are you trying to do a deal with me?
Because if you are,

31:32.600 --> 31:34.125
you must be explicit.

31:34.280 --> 31:36.009
I want your word

31:36.240 --> 31:39.562
that Tommy Shelby will not be
harmed if the guns are recovered.

31:39.720 --> 31:43.281
Your word as a gentleman.
Will you give it?

31:43.480 --> 31:45.482
Now, why would you want to save him?

31:47.840 --> 31:51.731
- Residue of sympathy.
- Sympathy? You mean, sentiment?

31:53.480 --> 31:56.962
Yes. In his way, he has been kind to me.

31:58.080 --> 32:00.162
- Sentiment.
- Yes.

32:07.200 --> 32:09.567
You're too good-hearted for this work.

32:10.960 --> 32:12.291
Perhaps.

32:13.640 --> 32:15.529
So, for my sake, will you spare him?

32:18.040 --> 32:19.644
You have my word.

32:23.760 --> 32:27.481
GRACE: A week after the robbery, there
was a burial at St Andrews' churchyard.

32:28.080 --> 32:31.402
I have found out that the man
supposed to be buried is alive.

32:32.320 --> 32:34.163
Arthur is quite concerned.

32:34.840 --> 32:38.083
I learned that the funeral
was attended only by the brothers,

32:39.240 --> 32:42.050
and the grave that they dug
was far deeper than your average,

32:42.440 --> 32:46.206
and lined with lead
to keep out the damp.

32:49.520 --> 32:52.000
The guns are buried in that grave.

32:53.760 --> 32:56.286
Then tonight we will dig up that grave.

32:58.840 --> 33:02.322
<i>GRACE: # When my family thinks</i>

33:02.560 --> 33:06.042
<i># That I'm safely in my bed</i>

33:06.280 --> 33:09.762
<i># Oh, from morn until night</i>

33:10.120 --> 33:13.966
<i># I am stretched out at your head</i>

33:14.320 --> 33:18.689
<i># flailing out unto the earth</i>

33:19.000 --> 33:22.482
<i># With tears hot and wild</i>

33:22.840 --> 33:27.323
<i># For the loss of a boy</i>

33:28.280 --> 33:31.762
<i># That I loved as a child</i>

33:34.000 --> 33:38.050
<i># So I am stretched on your grave</i>

33:38.320 --> 33:41.802
<i># And I'll lie here forever</i>

33:42.080 --> 33:45.562
<i># If your hands were in mine</i>

33:45.640 --> 33:49.690
<i># I'd be sure they would not sever</i>

33:50.360 --> 33:54.809
<i># My apple tree, my brightness</i>

33:55.720 --> 33:58.485
<i># It's time we were together</i>

33:58.560 --> 34:00.005
Well done, boys!

34:00.080 --> 34:03.562
<i># For I smell of the earth</i>

34:05.000 --> 34:09.050
<i># And I'm worn by the weather #</i>

34:18.600 --> 34:20.568
All but one gun accounted for.

34:31.080 --> 34:34.083
Then, sir, I resign my commission.

34:36.080 --> 34:38.889
Good... Good.

34:41.400 --> 34:45.324
So, I am no longer
your superior officer,

34:45.400 --> 34:48.882
and you're no longer my subordinate.

34:50.440 --> 34:52.647
And therefore...

34:54.080 --> 34:58.244
Regulations permit me
to offer you this.

35:06.400 --> 35:10.530
I'm a simple man, but a good man.

35:11.840 --> 35:16.562
And my admiration for you
has turned to love.

35:18.720 --> 35:21.371
I don't ask for love in return,

35:22.400 --> 35:25.483
just recognition that
we are like minds,

35:26.560 --> 35:28.449
with shared values.

35:29.840 --> 35:30.887
Grace...

35:32.760 --> 35:34.410
Will you marry me?

35:47.200 --> 35:48.611
Mr Campbell...

35:53.000 --> 35:54.331
You deserve better.

36:06.000 --> 36:07.889
Is it him between us?

36:08.640 --> 36:11.405
Is it the beast that dug that grave?

36:11.480 --> 36:12.891
(LOUDLY) Is it him?

36:14.680 --> 36:16.967
My resignation will be
with you in the morning.

36:29.480 --> 36:31.130
(TRAIN WHISTLES)

36:36.920 --> 36:38.046
Dad?

36:42.160 --> 36:43.207
Hello, son.

36:44.200 --> 36:46.487
May I ask who gave you my whereabouts?

36:46.560 --> 36:50.645
Marsden. Said you left him last night
with a bill for your whores.

36:50.720 --> 36:53.530
Well... At least we got
to say goodbye, son.

36:54.760 --> 36:57.604
And bid a fond ad/euto
your dear brothers, would you?

36:59.000 --> 37:01.810
- How could you do this to us?
- Do what, son?

37:02.040 --> 37:04.202
All that stuff you said about...

37:04.880 --> 37:06.723
Shelby Casino...

37:08.160 --> 37:12.006
- And Atlantic City.
- Hmm, well, if the truth be told,

37:12.520 --> 37:16.525
I'm not so acquainted with that
promised land as I had thee believe.

37:19.840 --> 37:21.410
You're a fucking liar.

37:22.520 --> 37:23.806
And a thief.

37:24.120 --> 37:27.044
Now you give me back
my fucking money!

37:27.480 --> 37:30.051
Do not despise the thief

37:30.160 --> 37:33.642
who steals to satisfy his starvation.

37:34.440 --> 37:36.647
That's in the Holy Bible, son.

37:37.440 --> 37:40.683
And I have starved for so very long.

37:42.880 --> 37:45.247
Fair thee well, son.

37:48.960 --> 37:50.849
I waited for ya.

37:52.760 --> 37:53.807
I waited.

37:55.120 --> 37:56.485
(SHOUTS)

37:57.560 --> 37:59.688
Listen to me, boy.

38:00.240 --> 38:02.322
You're not in the prize ring now.

38:02.520 --> 38:04.966
Never put your hands on me again

38:05.040 --> 38:08.601
or I'll cut your fucking throat
and spread you on these tracks.

38:40.720 --> 38:42.131
(DOOR OPENS)

38:49.080 --> 38:50.605
Where's your father?

38:56.200 --> 38:58.521
I'm assuming he's frittering away
the 500 you took from us

38:58.600 --> 39:01.968
and put into his
thieving, whore-groping hands.

39:04.760 --> 39:06.410
What were you thinking?

39:07.520 --> 39:11.127
How dare you do something like that
without talking to Thomas or me?

39:14.640 --> 39:16.210
Does Tommy know?

39:25.120 --> 39:26.167
No.

39:26.880 --> 39:28.211
But you're going to tell him.

39:30.040 --> 39:31.724
You may take satisfaction

39:32.600 --> 39:34.284
in a great victory.

39:34.960 --> 39:38.089
A terrible consequence has been avoided.

39:39.320 --> 39:43.803
<i>Those guns that we dug up will never
be used to murder the innocent,</i>

39:44.600 --> 39:46.762
<i>or usurp the status qua.</i>

39:47.200 --> 39:49.202
<i>But even though we have solved a crime,</i>

39:49.280 --> 39:53.080
<i>we have, as yet,
failed to punish the criminal.</i>

39:53.840 --> 39:58.801
This man who dug this grave
has also dug his own.

39:58.920 --> 40:03.528
He has proved a deadly menace
to the King's peace.

40:03.720 --> 40:06.564
<i>And tonight we will strike him down.</i>

40:06.920 --> 40:10.049
<i>We will drive our swords
through his black heart.</i>

40:10.120 --> 40:13.966
<i>We will pursue him into
the rat holes that he infests.</i>

40:14.160 --> 40:15.764
And finally,

40:16.640 --> 40:19.564
we will rid this city of his kind.

40:19.760 --> 40:22.366
<i>Justice will be done.</i>

40:22.440 --> 40:24.044
<i>And will be seen to be done.</i>

40:25.840 --> 40:26.966
Amen.

40:29.960 --> 40:31.610
There's going to be trouble now, Finn.

40:32.360 --> 40:34.249
You look after yourself, do you hear me?

40:34.320 --> 40:36.209
I'm gonna be gone away for a while.

40:37.120 --> 40:38.360
Right. Go on.

40:46.000 --> 40:47.445
Right!

40:47.680 --> 40:50.365
Who wants to fucking fight?

40:50.560 --> 40:51.971
Fighting's over.

40:52.480 --> 40:54.209
We're closing up and moving on.

40:54.280 --> 40:56.567
I said, "Who wants to fucking fight?"

40:56.800 --> 41:01.124
My name is Arthur fucking Shelby.

41:05.840 --> 41:07.410
Who dares fight me?

41:07.880 --> 41:10.963
Go home, lad.
Before you catch yourself a spanking.

41:22.840 --> 41:24.171
My brother in Digbeth

41:24.240 --> 41:26.766
just said the police are coming down
from Deritend, in numbers.

41:27.360 --> 41:29.044
Asking for Tommy Shelby, by name.

41:30.920 --> 41:31.967
Shit.

41:42.640 --> 41:44.449
- I'm gonna have to lie low for a while.
- Why?

41:45.000 --> 41:46.445
I lost my bargaining power.

41:46.520 --> 41:48.682
This copper, it's just me and him now.

41:49.360 --> 41:50.646
When I get back,

41:52.200 --> 41:53.281
I wanna tell you some things.

41:53.360 --> 41:55.647
Harry said the police
are already in Digbeth.

41:55.720 --> 41:57.882
- Yeah.
- You took a chance coming here.

41:57.960 --> 41:59.564
Why?

41:59.640 --> 42:01.483
The police are in the lane, Tommy.

42:02.400 --> 42:03.481
Come with me.

43:17.760 --> 43:20.650
I'm looking for Thomas Shelby.

43:28.840 --> 43:30.126
Never heard of him.

43:35.880 --> 43:37.450
You'll never find him.

43:45.680 --> 43:46.727
Go home.

43:54.320 --> 43:56.687
Perhaps I should ask
that question again.

43:58.040 --> 43:59.246
On your knees.

43:59.320 --> 44:00.924
(GRUNTS)

44:05.760 --> 44:06.807
Aye.

44:06.880 --> 44:08.962
Understand this, barman,

44:09.600 --> 44:11.682
I don't care if you live or die.

44:12.160 --> 44:13.491
I don't know!

44:14.240 --> 44:15.605
(HARRY SHUDDERS)

44:21.680 --> 44:22.727
(GUN CLICKS)

44:24.160 --> 44:25.207
He left.

44:26.520 --> 44:27.806
With the barmaid.

44:29.440 --> 44:30.771
He left with Grace.

44:32.760 --> 44:35.001
I think they were going to her place.

44:42.840 --> 44:44.205
Call it off.

44:45.040 --> 44:47.247
I don't understand, sir,
we should find the barmaid and...

44:47.320 --> 44:48.446
Call it off!

44:50.040 --> 44:51.121
All of it.

44:53.720 --> 44:54.767
Get in!

45:11.200 --> 45:13.168
It's not much of a place.

45:14.040 --> 45:15.201
It's all right.

45:15.640 --> 45:17.802
- Wa nt tea?
- Tea, no.

45:18.600 --> 45:20.170
I have rum.

45:20.360 --> 45:22.044
Actually, tea it is.

45:22.320 --> 45:24.641
- Trying to impress me?
- Yes.

45:25.040 --> 45:26.405
And do you have biscuits?

45:26.720 --> 45:28.404
No, they attract mice.

45:30.280 --> 45:31.930
People look different at home.

45:32.240 --> 45:33.287
In what way?

45:34.080 --> 45:35.570
Off guard.

45:39.040 --> 45:40.280
Should I be on my guard?

45:40.360 --> 45:41.407
No.

45:41.600 --> 45:43.329
I'm a man who drinks tea.

45:56.960 --> 45:59.201
When the trouble dies down, I'll go.

46:06.560 --> 46:08.562
When will it die down, do you think?

46:09.440 --> 46:11.090
Late, I'd say.

46:14.640 --> 46:16.290
So not until the morning then.

46:18.760 --> 46:21.047
Yes, I'd say I'll be here till morning.

46:28.520 --> 46:29.601
You have a gramophone.

46:29.680 --> 46:30.841
It's broken.

46:30.920 --> 46:32.285
We could still dance.

46:37.200 --> 46:38.247
Yes, why not?

46:44.360 --> 46:46.362
I know you like to be asked properly.

46:49.040 --> 46:50.804
Grace, can I have this dance?

49:03.600 --> 49:04.886
<i>GRACE: Are you okay?</i>

49:05.880 --> 49:08.281
<i>TOMMY". I don't hear
the shovels against the wall.</i>

49:10.520 --> 49:11.601
What shovels?

49:15.880 --> 49:17.291
Will you help me?

49:19.400 --> 49:20.765
Help you with what?

49:20.840 --> 49:22.126
With everything.

49:23.480 --> 49:25.084
The whole fucking thing.

49:25.880 --> 49:27.120
Fucking life.

49:28.120 --> 49:29.326
Business.

49:31.800 --> 49:33.325
I found you.

49:35.200 --> 49:36.531
And you found me.

49:39.600 --> 49:41.125
We'll help each other.

50:03.280 --> 50:05.203
(# <i>TIME</i> BY TOM WAITS PLAYING)

50:31.880 --> 50:32.927
(CRIES OUT)

50:55.880 --> 50:57.291
Our father,

50:58.240 --> 50:59.651
who art in Heaven,

51:01.000 --> 51:02.889
hallowed be thy name...

51:04.040 --> 51:05.769
(INHALES DEEPLY)

51:07.400 --> 51:09.368
(CHOKES AND COUGHS)

51:33.240 --> 51:34.685
(CHOKES)

51:35.720 --> 51:36.767
(GAS P5)

51:37.640 --> 51:39.005
(gouens)

51:52.600 --> 51:53.931
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

51:57.400 --> 51:58.890
Hello? (CLEARS THROAT)

52:01.320 --> 52:03.288
Send a telegram to Mr Churchill.

52:04.200 --> 52:06.441
I have news, very good news.

52:08.120 --> 52:11.920
<i>Tell him the business I came
to attend to is now complete.</i>

52:12.920 --> 52:14.649
<i>I'll be leaving the city.</i>

52:15.600 --> 52:20.128
<i>There's just one matter
I need to tidy up first.</i>

52:20.200 --> 52:21.406
(BELL TOLLING)

52:36.520 --> 52:37.567
(DOOR OPENS)

53:00.160 --> 53:01.844
So Polly told ya.

53:03.480 --> 53:04.527
Yup.

53:17.640 --> 53:19.165
You should've used a gun.

53:21.920 --> 53:23.843
Are you laughing at me, Tommy?

53:24.200 --> 53:25.247
Yeah.

53:27.400 --> 53:30.290
Just when things are
starting to go right, Arthur,

53:30.920 --> 53:32.570
you try and do this.

53:35.360 --> 53:37.203
Don't you like fancy parties?

53:37.800 --> 53:39.165
Or, um...

53:39.680 --> 53:42.490
Champagne? Or fast cars?

53:44.320 --> 53:45.765
And how about this?

53:50.840 --> 53:53.047
Your name on a business card.

53:53.200 --> 53:56.921
"Shelby Brothers, Limited.

53:57.520 --> 53:58.931
"Arthur Shelby.

53:59.040 --> 54:00.690
"Associate bookmaker."

54:00.800 --> 54:01.881
(SCOFFS)

54:01.960 --> 54:04.281
I just had them picked up
from the printer's this morning.

54:04.760 --> 54:07.331
You are one of three shareholders.

54:08.680 --> 54:10.444
Me, you, john.

54:10.640 --> 54:13.450
And according to the law,
we are equal partners.

54:13.640 --> 54:16.689
And it is written in
the paperwork in black and white.

54:17.040 --> 54:20.089
A third, a third, a third.

54:21.520 --> 54:22.601
(TOMMY EXHALES)

54:23.320 --> 54:24.731
But the thing is, uh...

54:24.800 --> 54:28.009
Well, me and john, we quite fancy
splitting your share, so...

54:28.200 --> 54:31.090
just next time, use a gun, man.

54:31.520 --> 54:32.567
(LAUGHS)

54:35.600 --> 54:38.843
Our men at the station tell me
that copper is leaving town.

54:40.200 --> 54:41.565
We're in the clear.

54:44.840 --> 54:46.888
We are on our way
up in the world, brother.

54:49.720 --> 54:50.926
Believe me.

54:58.320 --> 54:59.924
(# BRINGIT ON BY NICK CAVE PLAYING)

